{"title":"BH GravelX R Focuses on Gravel Racing with Lighter, Simplified Carbon Frame","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bh-gravelx-r-focuses-on-gravel-racing-with-lighter-simplified-carbon-frame/","date":1722621662000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike\" /></p>\n<p>BH expands on their micro-suspension GravelX gravel bike with a new lighter, faster GravelX R race bike that pares back to the essentials for racing. No comfort extras, just all the pure performance features to make this BH’s fastest-ever gravel race bike. Lightweight, stiff, aerodynamic, and with all the integration you could want but not the hassles…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, riding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_dusty-riding-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/BH)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While the GravelX has always been BH’s all-rounder gravel platform, its latest generation evolved with a strategically flexing rear end for all-day rough riding comfort. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But now, the BH GravelX R leaves extra comfort behind to focus more on racing. That’s what the <em>R</em> is there for.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, familiar styling\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_similar-front-end-768x576.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It inherits the same styling and overall outline of BH’s latest fast gravel bike – down to the bulbous headtube, dropped stays, and forward-swept “Air Bow” fork crown design. But it gets rid of the bump-eating pivoting seatstays &amp; flex chainstays of the regular <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bh-gravelx-carbon-gravel-race-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">GravelX</a> in a hunt for absolute speed.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, integrated cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_separate-but-integrated-cockpit-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You still get fully integrated internal cable routing through the headset, but the BH GravelX R keeps full position adjustability and serviceability with a separate alloy stem with a bolt-on cabling guide and a regular handlebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, non-driveside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_non-driveside-riding-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, the hollow core molded (HCIM) hi-mod carbon frame gets optimized for lighter weight and maximum race-ready stiffness.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, angled\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_angled-768x576.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>max 700c x 45mm tire clearance</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrated internal cable routing through the headtube, but with a separate bar &amp; ICR stem</li>\n\n\n\n<li>PressFit BB386 EVO bottom bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>hidden wedge-style seatpost clamp</li>\n\n\n\n<li>removable front derailleur mount &amp; conventional replaceable rear derailleur hanger</li>\n\n\n\n<li>5 standard 2-bolt bottle cage mounts: 2x downtube, 1x seattube, 2x fork legs </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible with the aero BH Toolbox that mounts below a set of matching aero water bottles</li>\n\n\n\n<li>12mm thru-axles, with hidden QR levers front &amp; rear</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_tradtional-derailleur-hanger.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_tradtional-derailleur-hanger.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, derailleur hanger\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_tradtional-derailleur-hanger.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_tradtional-derailleur-hanger-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_tradtional-derailleur-hanger-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_tradtional-derailleur-hanger-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_fork-mounts-but-smooth-sides.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_fork-mounts-but-smooth-sides.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, smooth dropouts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_fork-mounts-but-smooth-sides.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_fork-mounts-but-smooth-sides-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_fork-mounts-but-smooth-sides-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_fork-mounts-but-smooth-sides-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_QR-thru-axle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_QR-thru-axle.jpg\" alt=\"BH GravelX R light carbon gravel race bike, QR thru-axles\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_QR-thru-axle.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_QR-thru-axle-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_QR-thru-axle-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_QR-thru-axle-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>BH GravelX R gravel bike – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_geometry.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_geometry.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_geometry-297x119.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_geometry-120x48.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_geometry-768x307.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The all-new fast gravel BH GravelX R carbon race bike comes in 4 frame sizes (S-XL) and is offered in 4 bike builds.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"930\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x-1536x930.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, 3.5 GRX 1x12\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x-1536x930.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x-297x180.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x-768x465.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_3-5-GRX-1x.jpg 1900w\" /></a><figcaption>GravelX R 3.5 GRX 1×12</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"930\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x-1536x930.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, 5.5 GRX 2x12\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x-1536x930.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x-297x180.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x-768x465.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_5-5-GRX-2x.jpg 1900w\" /></a><figcaption>GravelX R 5.5 GRX2x12</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Complete bikes start at 3300€ for the GravelX R 3.5 with a wide Shimano GRX mechanical 1x 12sp (10-45T) groupset and alloy Vison TC30i wheels. Go 2×12 with the GravelX R 5.5 for 3500€ with its GRX 46/30T x 11-34T compact spread and the same wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1900\" height=\"1150\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, 4.5 Apex AXS\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS.jpg 1900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS-297x180.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS-1536x930.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_4-5-Apex-AXS-768x465.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>BH GravelX R 4.5 Apex AXS</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An electronic upgrade to SRAM Apex AXS Xplr 1×12 brings the cost of the GravelX R 4.5 to just 3700€, again with the same alloy wheelset.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1900\" height=\"1150\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, 6.5 GRX Di2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2.jpg 1900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2-297x180.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2-1536x930.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2-120x73.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_6-5-GRX-Di2-768x465.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>2024 BH GravelX R 6.5 GRX Di2 2×12</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Or, pick the top of the line with the 5000€ BH GravelX R 6.5 and you get a Shimano GRX Di2 2×12 electronic groupset and an upgrade to carbon Vision SC45 wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding.jpg\" alt=\"2024 BH GravelX R lightweight carbon gravel race bike, riding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2024-BH-GravelX-R-lightweight-carbon-gravel-race-bike_riding-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Most of the new gravel race bikes are available now via your local BH dealer. And then, the Di2 builds are expected to arrive in-store from September.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.bhbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BHbikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bh-gravelx-r-focuses-on-gravel-racing-with-lighter-simplified-carbon-frame/\">BH GravelX R Focuses on Gravel Racing with Lighter, Simplified Carbon Frame</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"dd6a9d77fee73128fa4664d773982dc68bcc988cd03455065957194790cf44eb","category":"Cycling"}